message.content: does privacy.com work with credit card accounts

content.thinking:

Privacy.com is a service that creates virtual debit cards, and it typically requires a bank account (checking account) or debit card to fund the virtual cards. It does not work with credit cards as a funding source for most users.

content.text:
No, Privacy.com does not work with credit card accounts as a funding source. 

Privacy.com creates virtual debit cards and requires you to link either:
- A bank account (checking account) via ACH
- A debit card

Credit cards cannot be used to fund Privacy.com virtual cards. This is because Privacy.com would essentially be facilitating a cash advance or money transfer from a credit card, which would involve cash advance fees and is generally restricted by card networks.

The service works by drawing funds directly from your linked bank account or debit card when charges are made to your Privacy virtual cards.
